Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Yes' radio button from Contrast enhanced box on Page 03
And I go to Page 06 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Ovary, mass' from the dropdown menu
And I select 'I describe' radio button

When I select 'Differential diagnosis' tab
Then 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Follicular cyst' from 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu
Then 'Hemorrhagic cyst' radio button is enabled
And 'Ovarian follicle' radio button is enabled
And 'Polycystic ovaries' radio button is enabled
And 'Corpus luteum cyst' radio button is enabled
And 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Fibroma' from 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu
Then 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cystadenofibroma' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Fibroma' from 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu
Then 'Cystadenofibroma' checkbox is enabled
And 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Follicular cyst' from 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu
Then 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hemorrhagic cyst' radio button is enabled
And 'Ovarian follicle' radio button is enabled
And 'Polycystic ovaries' radio button is enabled
And 'Corpus luteum cyst' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Oophoritis' from 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu
Then 'Tuboovarian abscess' checkbox is enabled
And  'Salpingitis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Metastasis' from 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu
Then 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hemorrhagic cyst' radio button is enabled
